Fresh Pi session: CODE REVIEW.

Inputs:
- User prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Design doc: {{run.dir}}/design/design.md
- Execution summary: {{run.dir}}/execution/summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Repository root: {{inputs.repo-root}}
- Base branch: {{inputs.base-branch}}

Goal:
Review the implementation against the prompt and design, then explicitly emit a pass/fail status artifact that controls the workflow route.

Rules:
- Do not edit source code.
- Review the diff against the base branch when available.
- Check for correctness, regressions, missing tests, security issues, and overbroad changes.
- Produce actionable issues only.
- If the implementation is acceptable, pass so the workflow can continue to PR drafting.
- If the implementation is not acceptable, fail and write issues so the workflow can merge them, increment the round, and return to execution.

Write:
- Report: {{run.dir}}/review/report-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/review/status-{{run.round}}.json
- If failing: {{run.dir}}/review/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Status JSON examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"review passed","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"review found issues","issues_file":"review/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}

Failure issues should be JSON matching the issues schema and should contain only actionable review findings for the next execution round.
